==German==
===Etymology===
From the older ''tartoffel'', which comes from {{It.}} ''[[tartuficolo]]''. This is a derivation of Middle Latin ''territuberum'' "[[truffle]]" (literally "ground tuber"). When potatoes arrived in Europe in the 16th century, people transferred older words to describe the new plant.

===Noun===
'''Kartoffel''' ''f'' (''pl'' Kartoffeln)
# a [[potato]]
